news.title: Mansion previously owned by China Evergrande's chairman sold for $57 million
news.para: The 5,000 sq ft (465 sq m) mansion located in a residential development on the Peak was seized by China Construction Bank (Asia) from Evergrande Chairman Hui Ka Yan in November 2022, via the appointment of receivers, according to the Land Registry records.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government halts cancellation of land allotment to M3M group in Noida
news.para: The UP government had on May 10 cancelled the allotment of plots located in Noida's Sector 72 and Sector 94 on grounds that the allotment through e-tender process was done in violation of rules. Subsequently, the Noida Authority had sealed the project sites.

news.title: About 131 societies in Noida lack proper fire safety equipment
news.para: The fire department in GB Nagar identified 131 highrises lacking proper fire-fighting equipment, leading to concerns about fire incidents and safety measures in Noida and Greater Noida.

news.title: Delhi civic body expedites work on projects under village initiative
news.para: However, the election process caused delays, resulting in only eight projects being started. The remaining projects are pending due to the absence of finalised agencies to carry out the work.

news.title: West Bengal CM rolls out survey of people eligible for Awas Yojana
news.para: Banerjee, sources said, focused on ensuring timely delivery of poll promises and monitoring of ongoing projects. She emphasised the importance of cost curtailment and timely completion of projects, including the Ghatal Master Plan and various bridge works.

news.title: Gurugram: DLF-2 residents protest against authorities over water crisis
news.para: Holding posters, empty buckets, and earthen pots in the scorching heat, the protesters said their colony has been facing a severe water crisis since April, forcing them to hit the streets.

news.title: Goa eases sale deed registration for Goans with foreign nationality
news.para: A senior officer said that there were a lot of cases where the sub-registrars were reluctant to register deeds belonging to Goans who have acquired foreign nationality and govt felt that the process to register properties should be simplified.

news.title: Will Aravalis get a definition by August 2024?
news.para: Haryana forest officials said on Tuesday that the panel will study the report of Forest Survey of India (FSI) submitted to the Central Empowered Committee (CEC) on its endorsed definition of the ancient hills, along with Rajasthan’s criteria.

news.title: WeWork's CEO steps down as company exits bankruptcy
news.para: The company named commercial real estate industry veteran John Santora as its new top boss. He most recently served as Tri-State chairman at global real estate services firm Cushman & Wakefield.

news.title: NCLAT asks ICICI to consider Jaiprakash Associates' one-time settlement proposal
news.para: Insolvency appellate tribunal NCLAT has asked ICICI Bank to consider bankrupt Jaiprakash Associates Ltd's (JAL) one-time settlement proposal to clear its outstanding loans.

news.title: Yamuna Expressway authority to revise its e-auction policy
news.para: According to the current rule, bids are extended twice — by seven days each — if only one applicant takes part in the tendering process.

news.title: One-time settlement for property tax in Bengaluru till July 31: Karnataka deputy CM
news.para: The one-time settlement (OTS) scheme will end on July 31 and hence I urge people to make use of the opportunity to clear the outstanding payments," said Shivakumar.

news.title: China's Dexin ordered to liquidate by Hong Kong court
news.para: Dexin joined the growing ranks of Chinese developers under pressure from creditors in the aftermath of a years-long crisis in China's property market.

news.title: Organised paints sector to double production capacity by FY27: Crisil
news.para: A large part of this, around 2.4 blpa will be operational this fiscal, with the new player alone adding 1.3 blpa, primarily in the decorative segment, which accounts for 75-80% of the total production.

news.title: Chandrababu Naidu announces Amaravati as sole capital city of Andhra Pradesh
news.para: ​​"In our government, there will be no games under the guise of three capitals. Our capital is Amaravati. Amaravati is the capital," asserted Chandrababu Naidu.

news.title: MoEngage increases seating capacity to 900 with 315Work Avenue
news.para: The firm has doubled its capacity to 900 seats. The office space is located in Koramangala, Bangalore, spanning approximately 45,000 square feet.

news.title: Jaipur: RIICO holds back conversion of Manpur Machedi zone, senses realty bonanza
news.para: ​In fact, the conversion, which exponentially escalates the land prices, benefiting the plot owners, has been under scrutiny of the current govt, as the decision was taken during the final six months of the previous administration.

news.title: Shivraj Singh Chouhan is rural development minister, panchayati raj goes to Lalan Singh
news.para: The panchayati raj ministry, which was created first in 2004, looks after transferring grants to rural local bodies for civic programmes and their functioning.

news.title: CREDAI wants UP-RERA to reconsider order which made OC a must for possession letter
news.para: "The UP RERA needs to reconsider this decision in the benefit of homebuyers," said CREDAI western Uttar Pradesh Secretary Dinesh Gupta.

news.title: UK Consulate buys nearly 15,000 sq ft office in Mumbai's Lower Parel
news.para: The UK Consulate has acquired the office space spread across a total 12 units on the 19th floor of the tower from Lodha Group’s listed entity Macrotech Developers.
